  "prompt": "What is the most underrated romantic movie?",
  "response": "Determining the \"most underrated\" romantic movie can be quite subjective, as preferences for storytelling styles, genres, and emotional tones vary widely among audiences. However, one film that frequently surfaces in discussions about underrated romances is **\"The Spectacular Now\" (2013)**.\n\n### **The Spectacular Now (2013)**\n**Director:** James Ponsoldt  \n**Starring:** Miles Teller, Shailene Woodley\n\n**Why It's Underrated:**\n\"The Spectacular Now\" offers a refreshing and realistic portrayal of teenage romance and personal growth. Unlike many romantic films that idealize relationships, this movie delves into the complexities of young love, self-discovery, and the challenges of transitioning into adulthood. Miles Teller delivers a compelling performance as Sutter Keely, a charismatic yet troubled high school senior whose carefree attitude masks deeper insecurities. Shailene Woodley complements him beautifully as Aimee Finecky, whose quiet strength and introspection provide a grounding balance.\n\nThe film stands out for its authentic dialogue, nuanced character development, and its willingness to address serious themes such as alcoholism and the impact of past traumas on present relationships. Despite critical acclaim, including a nomination for Best Adapted Screenplay at the Academy Awards, \"The Spectacular Now\" didn't achieve widespread mainstream recognition, making it a beloved gem among those who have discovered it.\n\n### **Other Notable Underrated Romantic Films:**\n\n1. **\"Once\" (2007)**\n   - A heartfelt musical romance that explores the deep connection between two aspiring musicians in Dublin. Its minimalistic approach and genuine chemistry make it a standout.\n\n2. **\"About Time\" (2013)**\n   - While it has a dedicated fan base, \"About Time\" masterfully blends romance with time-travel elements to explore love, family, and the importance of living in the moment.\n\n3. **\"The Adjustment Bureau\" (2011)**\n   - This film combines romance with a sci-fi twist, depicting a love story challenged by mysterious forces controlling fate. Its unique premise and engaging performances make it a hidden treasure.\n\n4. **\"Sing Street\" (2016)**\n   - Set in 1980s Dublin, this coming-of-age musical romance follows a teenager who starts a band to impress a girl. Its vibrant soundtrack and heartfelt narrative resonate with many viewers.\n\n5. **\"Warm Bodies\" (2013)**\n   - An unconventional take on romance set in a post-apocalyptic world, where a zombie experiences a transformation through love. Its originality and charm have earned it a dedicated following.\n\n### **Conclusion**\n\nWhile mainstream romantic movies often receive the most attention, there are numerous films like \"The Spectacular Now\" that offer profound and authentic explorations of love and relationships. These underrated gems provide fresh perspectives and emotional depth, making them well worth seeking out for any romance enthusiast.",
